&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6506&quot; title=&quot;PropertiesFileInitialContextFactory pollutes system properties with values that may contain passwords&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-6506&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-6506&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6508&quot; title=&quot;PropertiesFileInitialContextFactory silences important exceptions and is non-compliant with the InitialContext interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-6508&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-6508&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Java Client&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; PropertiesFileInitialContextFactory no longer swallows exceptions, pollutes the system properties, nor modifies the environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IOExceptions and URISyntaxExceptions that were previously swallowed are now chained to a NamingException.&lt;br/&gt;
If the environment needs to be modified within the method a copy is created.&lt;br/&gt;
System properties are no longer set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;work done by Lorenz Quack &amp;lt;quack.lorenz@gmail.com&amp;gt; and Keith Wall &amp;lt;kwall@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
